Okay it works great.  Just enter the Pablo/nop in the Registered to section and then add serial number.  Then hit enter or click the red button to close it.  Then click on the quicktime in the dock and then go to the top under quicktime player and click the about quicktime and it will say quicktime pro version 7.1

You can do more things in pro, check out this link to read more about pro:

http://www.apple.com/ca/quicktime/pro/mac.html

it was great. all you got to do is... go to Quicktime 7 under your applications. Open it. Go to registration.. under "Quicktime player" and enter all the info. After that all you got to do is close it. The way you know you did it is by Going back to "Quicktime Player" and  take a look at "About Quicktime Player" and it will have PRO under the "Quicktime" Logo. BTW not that hard!!!!!
